{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":22140,"name":"Trevor Cash","username":"TrevorCash","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/trevorcash/{size}/698_2.png","created_at":"2017-12-02T19:34:26.734Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI found myself wanting a basic tool for quickly adding debug geometry to my scene at any time using a single call and then having it disappear automatically later after a delay.  So I made a subsystem called VisualDebugger that wraps calls to DebugRenderer like DebugRenderer-\u0026gt;AddLine(‚Ä¶) etc.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003caside class=\"onebox githubblob\"\u003e\n  \u003cheader class=\"source\"\u003e\n      \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/TrevorCash/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/Graphics/VisualDebugger.h\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003egithub.com\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003c/header\u003e\n  \u003carticle class=\"onebox-body\"\u003e\n    \u003ch4\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/TrevorCash/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/Graphics/VisualDebugger.h\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eTrevorCash/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/Graphics/VisualDebugger.h\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h4\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-h\"\u003e#ifndef VISUAL_DEBUGGER_H\n#define VISUAL_DEBUGGER_H\n\n#include \"limits.h\"\n\n#include \"../Core/Object.h\"\n#include \"../Core/Timer.h\"\n#include \"../Container/List.h\"\n#include \"../Math/Sphere.h\"\n#include \"../Math/Polyhedron.h\"\n#include \"../Math/Frustum.h\"\n#include \"../Math/Ray.h\"\n#include \"../Scene/Node.h\"\n\nnamespace Urho3D\n{\n\tclass DebugRenderer;\n\tclass Camera;\n\tclass Text;\n\tclass Node;\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\n  This file has been truncated. \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/TrevorCash/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/Graphics/VisualDebugger.h\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eshow original\u003c/a\u003e\n\n  \u003c/article\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"onebox-metadata\"\u003e\n    \n    \n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"clear: both\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eInitialization/setup:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRegisterSubsystem(new VisualDebugger(context_));\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSpecify camera for displaying labels in the world:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGetSubsystem\u0026lt;VisualDebugger\u0026gt;()-\u0026gt;SetPrimaryCamera(camera);\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn HandlePostRenderUpdate() Issue the draw call to draw all geometry:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGetSubsystem\u0026lt;VisualDebugger\u0026gt;()-\u0026gt;DrawDebugGeometry(scene_-\u0026gt;GetComponent\u0026lt;DebugRenderer\u0026gt;());\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eExample Usage anywhere:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eVisualDebuggerUILabel* label = GetSubsystem\u0026lt;VisualDebugger\u0026gt;()-\u0026gt;AddLabel(Vector3(0,0,0), ‚Äúmy debug label in the world‚Äù);\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBy default geometry will last 2 seconds until it is deleted.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis can be changed with a call to SetObjectLifeTimeMs() Or by calling label-\u0026gt;SetLifeTimeMs() for individual control.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou can also restrict the max number of draw-able objects and/or the maximum time spent in the DrawDebugGeometry() call.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-02-15T17:32:26.877Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":15,"reads":51,"readers_count":50,"score":205.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":3814,"topic_slug":"visualdebugger-subsystem","display_username":"Trevor Cash","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":5,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/Trevor